cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper discusses machine learning methods for learning from recommender system logs, which involves optimizing decision rules based on historical data. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses methods for estimating the performance of different policies, which involves importance sampling and variance reduction techniques, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on recommender systems, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
